# Postgres connection string (Neon or Vercel Postgres).
# Copy to .env.local and fill in your URL. Run lib/db/schema.sql once in your database.
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@host/database?sslmode=require

# Supabase Storage (recommended, free tier) – for admin Media uploads.
# 1. Create a project at https://supabase.com 2. Project Settings → API: copy URL and service_role key.
# 3. Storage: create a bucket named "media", set it to Public.
# SUPABASE_URL=https://xxxx.supabase.co
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=eyJ...
# SUPABASE_MEDIA_BUCKET=media

# Supabase Auth – for Google/Apple sign-in. Use the same project URL and the anon (public) key from API.
# In Supabase: Authentication → Providers → enable Google and/or Apple; URL Configuration → add redirect URL: https://yourdomain.com/auth/callback (and http://localhost:3000/auth/callback for dev).
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://xxxx.supabase.co
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJ...

# Moyasar Payments — Invoice (hosted payment link)
# Server creates an invoice and redirects the customer to Moyasar’s checkout URL.
# Same API for test and live: the secret key selects the environment (sk_test_ vs sk_live_).
#
# Local / staging (no real charges):
# MOYASAR_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_...
#
# Production (real cards — real charges):
# 1. Complete Moyasar live onboarding in the dashboard (business verification, etc.).
# 2. Vercel → Project → Settings → Environment Variables → Production:
#    MOYASAR_SECRET_KEY=sk_live_...
# 3. Keep sk_test_ on Preview/Development so preview deploys never charge real cards.
# 4. Site must use HTTPS. Callback URLs use your request host automatically.
# 5. In Moyasar, allow webhook/callback: https://yourdomain.com/api/moyasar/invoice-webhook
#
# Webhook: register https://yourdomain.com/api/moyasar/invoice-webhook if Moyasar asks for it.

# Vercel Blob – optional fallback if Supabase is not set. Create a Blob store in Vercel Dashboard.
# BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN=
